en: Her excuse added up to nothing.
zh: 她的借口毫无意义。

en: What she wants to say just adds up to a refusal.
zh: 她想说的话实际上就是拒绝。

en: I get a kick out of her cheerful personality.
zh: 我喜欢她开朗的性格。

en: Her studies are improving slowly but steadily.
zh: 她的学习正在缓慢但稳步地进步。

en: Her dog is not so much faithful as tame.
zh: 她的狗与其说是忠诚，不如说是驯服。

en: It is a pity that she should be in such poor health.
zh: 很遗憾她的健康状况如此糟糕。

en: Her health is becoming steadily better.
zh: 她的健康状况正在稳步好转。

en: Her health isn't equal to that heavy task.
zh: 她的健康状况无法胜任这项繁重的工作。

en: When will her wedding be held?
zh: 她的婚礼什么时候举行？

en: I tried to change her mind, but I couldn't.
zh: 我试图改变她的想法，但我做不到。

en: Her weakness is that she talks too much.
zh: 她的缺点是她话太多。

en: I love her none the less for her faults.
zh: 我仍然爱她，尽管她有缺点。

en: With all her faults, I like her.
zh: 尽管她有缺点，我还是喜欢她。

en: With all her faults, I still like her.
zh: 尽管她有缺点，我仍然喜欢她。

en: She was over thirty when her artistic talent emerged.
zh: 她的艺术天赋在她三十多岁时才显现出来。

en: Despite her warning, he made little of the matter.
zh: 尽管她发出了警告，他还是轻视了这件事。

en: You should have paid attention to her warning.
zh: 你本应该注意她的警告。

en: Her brother is a good driver.
zh: 她的哥哥是个好司机。

en: I suppose her brother would be about forty when he died.
zh: 我猜她哥哥去世的时候大概四十岁左右。

en: They had decided to put the wedding off until her brother came home from abroad.
zh: 他们已经决定推迟婚礼，直到她的哥哥从国外回来。

en: Don't be taken in by her crocodile tears.
zh: 不要被她的鳄鱼的眼泪所迷惑。

en: I'm fed up with her grumbling.
zh: 我厌倦了她的抱怨。

en: She irritates me to no end with her complaints.
zh: 她的抱怨让我烦恼不已。

en: All her money went to her nephew.
zh: 她所有的钱都给了她的侄子。

en: Her neighbors were such as you meet everywhere in this country.
zh: 她的邻居就像你在全国各地都能遇到的人一样。

en: The students around her were talking about the test.
zh: 她周围的学生都在谈论考试。

en: Her diligence is indeed worthy of praise.
zh: 她的勤奋确实值得称赞。

en: Her diligence is a good example to us all.
zh: 她的勤奋是我们所有人的好榜样。

en: Her heart was hammering.
zh: 她的心怦怦直跳。

en: Her heart jumped for joy.
zh: 她的心欢快地跳了起来。

en: Her heart was full of joy.
zh: 她的心里充满了喜悦。

en: The fire of ambition burned within her.
zh: 她心中燃烧着雄心壮志的火焰。

en: Her heart flowed with gratitude.
zh: 她的心中充满了感激之情。

en: Her skill as a teacher is based on her understanding of young people.
zh: 她作为一名教师的技能是基于她对年轻人的理解。

en: Her ideas on education are very different from mine.
zh: 她对教育的看法和我的很不一样。

en: She was on the verge of fainting out of sheer terror.
zh: 她差点因为极度的恐惧而昏倒。

en: Her fears gradually quietened down.
zh: 她的恐惧逐渐平息下来。

en: In answer to her shouts, people ran to help her.
zh: 听到她的呼喊，人们跑去帮助她。

en: Her scream brought the police.
zh: 她的尖叫声引来了警察。

en: Her suitors were all after her money.
zh: 她的追求者都是冲着她的钱来的。

en: Her classmates folded three hundred and fifty-six cranes so that one thousand were buried with her.
zh: 她的同学们折了三百五十六只纸鹤，以便和她一起埋葬一千只。

en: I was numbed by her sudden death.
zh: 她的突然去世让我麻木了。

en: Her application for leave was refused.
zh: 她的请假申请被拒绝了。

en: Her leave request was denied.
zh: 她的请假请求被拒绝了。

en: Her argument was not built on facts.
zh: 她的论点不是建立在事实基础上的。

en: Her argument was not based on facts.
zh: 她的论点不是基于事实的。

en: Nothing has resulted from her prayer.
zh: 她的祈祷没有任何结果。

en: Her mood graduated to irritation.
zh: 她的情绪逐渐转为恼怒。

en: There was no changing her mind.
zh: 无法改变她的想法。

en: Don't ignore her feelings.
zh: 不要忽视她的感受。

en: She dazzles everybody with her wit.
zh: 她的机智使每个人都感到惊艳。

en: Her wish is to become a good teacher.
zh: 她的愿望是成为一名好老师。

en: All her hopes have vanished.
zh: 她所有的希望都破灭了。

en: So great was her joy that she shed tears.
zh: 她欣喜若狂，流下了眼泪。

en: Such was her joy that she shed tears.
zh: 她欣喜若狂，流下了眼泪。

en: Such was her delight that she fainted.
zh: 她欣喜若狂，晕了过去。

en: Her request never reached me.
zh: 她的请求从未到达我这里。

en: Her request never reached its intended recipient.
zh: 她的请求从未到达预期的接收者手中。

en: Asked to do her a favor, he completely ignored it.
zh: 请他帮她一个忙，他完全无视了。

en: Her wish is to study abroad someday.
zh: 她的愿望是有一天能出国留学。

en: Her wish was realized at last.
zh: 她的愿望最终实现了。

en: Her face betrayed her real feelings.
zh: 她的表情暴露了她真实的感受。

en: I know her by sight, but I've never spoken to her.
zh: 我见过她，但我从未和她说过话。

en: We associate her face with a rose.
zh: 我们将她的脸与玫瑰联系起来。

en: We associate her face with a cherry.
zh: 我们将她的脸与樱桃联系起来。

en: I was unable to look her in the face.
zh: 我无法正视她。
